WEBVTT

00:00.174 --> 00:05.122
♪ Hey, why is it happening ♪

00:06.094 --> 00:08.802
♪ My heart is racing ♪

00:09.934 --> 00:13.942
♪ The world has fallen silent ♪

00:13.966 --> 00:18.722
♪ Hey, when I imagine you ♪

00:19.758 --> 00:22.786
♪ What kind of look ♪

00:23.790 --> 00:27.734
♪ Attracted me to you ♪

00:27.758 --> 00:31.030
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:31.054 --> 00:34.518
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

00:34.542 --> 00:39.790
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

00:39.790 --> 00:41.408
♪ I love you ♪

00:41.408 --> 00:44.886
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:44.910 --> 00:48.182
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

00:48.206 --> 00:53.878
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

00:53.902 --> 00:55.246
♪ I love you ♪

00:55.246 --> 00:58.582
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:58.606 --> 01:01.954
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

01:02.062 --> 01:07.259
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

01:07.259 --> 01:08.942
♪ I love you ♪

01:08.942 --> 01:12.342
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

01:12.366 --> 01:15.766
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

01:15.790 --> 01:21.366
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

01:21.390 --> 01:24.802
♪ I love you ♪

01:27.080 --> 01:27.870
=Love Me, Love My Voice=

01:27.870 --> 01:30.846
=Love Me, Love My Voice=
=Episode 8=

01:30.846 --> 01:34.358
(I like you a lot.
Will you be my girlfriend?)

01:50.097 --> 01:52.037
I heard
that you signed a contract today.

01:53.218 --> 01:54.482
Yes, I did.

02:01.538 --> 02:03.237
How was it? Did it go well?

02:04.298 --> 02:05.557
Very.

02:06.098 --> 02:09.010
It was kind of a thrill
to be fully trusted.

02:09.818 --> 02:11.957
What a great partner indeed!

02:13.098 --> 02:15.437
And, you know...

02:18.578 --> 02:19.918
What are you doing?

02:22.018 --> 02:24.530
Get up early tomorrow
and buy groceries with me.

02:24.606 --> 02:27.878
Let's finish recording the 20 lines
of the game's dialogue tonight.

02:28.978 --> 02:30.130
Okay.

02:31.858 --> 02:33.010
Let's do it.

02:34.418 --> 02:37.038
We'll start in ten minutes.
I'll warm up first.

02:38.258 --> 02:40.798
Alright, time to get to work.

02:41.978 --> 02:43.837
Here we go.

02:55.777 --> 03:00.758
Mom, I'm not eating at home tonight.

03:02.538 --> 03:04.897
The celery I bought today
is really fresh.

03:04.897 --> 03:06.617
I was planning to make you some wontons.

03:06.617 --> 03:08.198
Are you going back to school?

03:09.378 --> 03:11.314
I'm going to a classmate's place.

03:11.858 --> 03:13.858
Don't you need
to go back to school today?

03:13.858 --> 03:14.957
I have no classes.

03:15.617 --> 03:16.878
No?

03:18.298 --> 03:22.298
Then go to the supermarket
and grab some snacks.

03:22.298 --> 03:25.418
You can't go to your classmate's place
empty-handed.

03:25.418 --> 03:27.478
Okay. Thanks, mom. Gotta go.

03:41.122 --> 03:42.642
(Jiayuan)

04:00.798 --> 04:01.378
Thank you.

04:01.378 --> 04:02.598
Don't mention it.

04:23.618 --> 04:25.518
1602.

04:28.417 --> 04:29.977
East Wind!

04:29.977 --> 04:31.977
Wait a minute. I think I won.

04:31.977 --> 04:33.337
I've won. I've won.

04:33.337 --> 04:34.457
Wait, how did you win this?

04:34.457 --> 04:35.818
It's an East Wind, right?

04:35.818 --> 04:37.297
No, that's not correct.

04:37.297 --> 04:38.657
You have Six and Seven, but not Nine.

04:38.657 --> 04:40.217
This is a false win.

04:40.217 --> 04:41.698
I don't want to play with you anymore.

04:41.698 --> 04:43.618
- Somebody's ringing the doorbell.
- Who is it?

04:43.618 --> 04:44.578
I'll go. It's the delivery.

04:44.578 --> 04:45.498
You go. Open the door.

04:45.498 --> 04:46.657
What delivery?

04:46.657 --> 04:48.198
Who ordered it?

04:49.897 --> 04:52.738
Sheng, you've arrived so early.
Ah, you shouldn't have brought these.

04:52.738 --> 04:54.417
We're playing mahjong.
Mo's in the kitchen.

04:54.417 --> 04:55.138
I'm killing them.

04:55.138 --> 04:56.818
- Sheng's here!
- Sheng's here!

04:56.818 --> 04:57.777
Come in, Sheng.

04:57.777 --> 04:58.897
Come on in.

04:58.897 --> 04:59.897
Is it cold outside? Come in.

04:59.897 --> 05:00.578
You bought snacks.

05:00.578 --> 05:02.797
Mo has specially prepared
these slippers for you.

05:03.657 --> 05:04.537
Thank you.

05:04.537 --> 05:06.297
You two should learn from her.

05:06.297 --> 05:08.857
You live off of others every day
without even contributing food.

05:08.857 --> 05:10.058
Give me the backpack.

05:10.058 --> 05:11.678
Okay, thank you.

05:13.618 --> 05:14.417
Make yourself at home.

05:14.417 --> 05:16.657
If you keep playing like that,
I won't play with you anymore.

05:16.657 --> 05:19.378
Sheng is here.
Can we turn on the air conditioner now?

05:19.938 --> 05:21.330
Of course. Turn it on.

05:21.857 --> 05:22.818
Well, now that Sheng's here.

05:22.818 --> 05:24.857
That's purely a double standard.

05:24.857 --> 05:27.777
Look, I'm frozen to death.

05:27.777 --> 05:29.118
Come on, Sheng.

05:30.097 --> 05:32.417
Try these strawberries.
I just washed them. They're very sweet.

05:32.417 --> 05:33.957
Okay, thank you.

05:36.618 --> 05:38.498
- They are really sweet.
- Right?

05:38.498 --> 05:41.537
Now that Sheng is here,
can we try some too?

05:41.537 --> 05:44.198
Okay, now you're allowed to have one.

05:44.818 --> 05:46.217
- Thank you.
- Dirty hands.

05:46.217 --> 05:47.250
Right.

05:50.097 --> 05:51.897
Sheng, why don't you join us
to play mahjong?

05:51.897 --> 05:52.618
Can you play?

05:52.618 --> 05:54.138
Come on and try. You can replace him.

05:54.138 --> 05:55.857
He had four false wins
out of five rounds.

05:55.857 --> 05:58.758
That's unbearable, you know?

05:59.498 --> 06:02.258
Why didn't you call me before coming up?

06:02.258 --> 06:04.917
Someone opened the door downstairs.
So I came straight up.

06:05.457 --> 06:07.657
Isn't that good?
No need to be so formal.

06:07.657 --> 06:09.058
Exactly. Why so formal?

06:09.058 --> 06:11.138
How will we get along in the future
if you are so formal?

06:11.138 --> 06:12.097
You're not an outsider.

06:12.097 --> 06:13.417
Right.

06:13.417 --> 06:16.178
Sheng, do you want
to play mahjong with us

06:16.178 --> 06:17.897
or watch Mo cook?

06:17.897 --> 06:18.777
Play mahjong with us.

06:18.777 --> 06:21.698
- Quick.
- Take my place.

06:21.698 --> 06:24.717
I think I'd better help
with the cooking.

06:28.178 --> 06:29.058
Alright, then go.

06:29.058 --> 06:31.297
But I doubt you'll be of much help.

06:31.297 --> 06:33.518
You can go inside
and just watch him cook.

06:34.457 --> 06:35.538
Come in.

06:36.457 --> 06:37.138
What was that?

06:37.138 --> 06:39.578
What?
I told her to go in and take a break.

06:39.578 --> 06:42.058
Can I help with anything?

06:42.058 --> 06:44.337
Actually, there is no need.

06:44.337 --> 06:46.698
I can wash and cut vegetables.

06:46.698 --> 06:49.438
Do you want to drink something?
There's orange juice in the fridge.

06:50.750 --> 06:51.297
Okay.

06:51.297 --> 06:52.578
- I want to drink too.
- Me too.

06:52.578 --> 06:54.678
- Me too.
- I also want to drink orange juice.

06:58.138 --> 06:59.857
There are four boxes of orange juice
in the fridge.

06:59.857 --> 07:01.178
Help yourself if you want to drink it.

07:01.178 --> 07:02.878
If you don't, keep playing mahjong.

07:04.897 --> 07:06.457
What was the result
of the last round again?

07:06.457 --> 07:07.818
It was a false win. It's on him.

07:07.818 --> 07:09.837
You called a fake win,
and revealed my hand.

07:10.897 --> 07:12.277
The cups are at the top.

07:57.698 --> 07:59.638
Do you want some orange juice?

08:00.857 --> 08:02.078
Then...

08:03.698 --> 08:05.638
My hands are occupied.

08:13.217 --> 08:14.558
Well.

08:34.258 --> 08:35.378
All right.

08:37.218 --> 08:38.226
Thank you.

08:40.098 --> 08:41.138
You're welcome.

09:10.817 --> 09:11.958
Zhou Zheng.

09:13.618 --> 09:16.338
Please clean the dining table.
We are about to start cooking.

09:16.338 --> 09:17.478
Sure.

09:18.098 --> 09:21.238
Why not assign me something to do
as well?

09:22.657 --> 09:23.838
Are you sure?

09:25.657 --> 09:26.738
Then let's cook.

09:27.458 --> 09:28.498
Okay.

09:29.297 --> 09:32.358
It's crispy-skinned fish
in chili sauce. It's quite simple.

09:33.258 --> 09:37.358
First, make slits on both sides
of the fish like this.

09:39.657 --> 09:40.838
On this side too.

09:48.697 --> 09:49.718
Okay.

09:51.378 --> 09:55.338
Then add some salt to the mixture
of egg and starch prepared in advance.

09:55.338 --> 09:56.358
About this much.

09:57.657 --> 10:01.598
After mixing,
apply it all over the fish.

10:09.738 --> 10:11.297
When we start cooking later,

10:11.297 --> 10:13.537
just put the entire fish into the pan.

10:13.537 --> 10:16.638
Fry it until it gets golden,
then take it out and put it on a plate.

10:17.258 --> 10:19.018
Leave some oil in the pan

10:19.018 --> 10:21.577
to stir-fry minced ginger and garlic
until they become fragrant.

10:21.577 --> 10:27.098
Then add chili, soy sauce, salt,
and sugar, and stir them well.

10:27.098 --> 10:30.518
Finally, pour the mixture onto the fish
with chopped chives.

10:32.138 --> 10:33.317
Isn't it simple?

10:34.498 --> 10:36.077
Did you remember it all?

10:37.297 --> 10:38.437
Almost.

10:47.297 --> 10:50.077
I am a doctor, you know.

10:52.018 --> 10:53.157
Yes, I know.

10:54.138 --> 10:55.598
My parents are too.

10:57.098 --> 10:59.177
We're always very busy

10:59.177 --> 11:01.277
and don't get to see each other often.

11:02.417 --> 11:06.838
So when I have some spare time,
I start doing voice-acting.

11:10.657 --> 11:14.238
I am not complicated.
I'm a simple person.

11:26.098 --> 11:28.677
Step back a bit.
Be careful not to burn yourself.

12:07.738 --> 12:10.498
See? It's the golden color we want.

12:10.498 --> 12:13.518
Don't fry it for too long,
or the fish will become tough.

12:26.738 --> 12:27.826
Sheng.

12:34.378 --> 12:37.397
The fish is fried until golden.

12:38.218 --> 12:43.917
Then stir-fry the ginger and garlic,
right?

13:01.458 --> 13:02.838
I like you a lot.

13:12.338 --> 13:13.838
Will you be my girlfriend?

13:25.657 --> 13:26.917
I'm serious.

13:34.577 --> 13:39.218
We've only met a few times.

13:39.218 --> 13:41.557
It has nothing to do
with how many times we've met.

13:59.537 --> 14:01.037
What if

14:03.057 --> 14:04.498
we're not suited for each other?

14:04.498 --> 14:06.077
And what if we are?

14:10.577 --> 14:11.797
If we don't start,

14:14.338 --> 14:16.037
we won't know the end,

14:20.498 --> 14:21.586
right?

14:47.218 --> 14:49.018
Use the oil from the bottom of the pan

14:49.018 --> 14:51.317
to stir-fry the ginger and garlic.

15:10.218 --> 15:11.277
Smells good?

15:14.018 --> 15:15.537
Yes.

15:15.537 --> 15:16.838
Eat more later.

15:18.297 --> 15:19.410
Okay.

15:49.417 --> 15:51.897
The table is set. Need any help?

15:51.897 --> 15:53.118
I'm almost done.

15:57.258 --> 15:59.077
Sheng, what's with your face?

16:00.937 --> 16:03.177
Look at you, Mo.
You've even turned Sheng's face red

16:03.177 --> 16:05.518
when frying the fish.

16:07.978 --> 16:10.118
Let me help you with the dishes.

16:15.378 --> 16:16.258
Well done, Mo.

16:16.258 --> 16:16.937
Okay.

16:16.937 --> 16:18.118
Here we go.

16:22.297 --> 16:24.917
- The food is coming.
- Nice.

16:26.657 --> 16:27.498
Great presentation.

16:27.498 --> 16:30.037
Alright, you can go out and wait.
It's a bit smoky in here.

16:36.657 --> 16:37.657
Here, Sheng, sit down.

16:37.657 --> 16:40.562
Come, Sheng. Sit between me and Doudou.

16:41.897 --> 16:45.057
Here, fish-flavored eggplant.
It goes really well with rice.

16:45.057 --> 16:46.657
This is really quite a feast.

16:46.657 --> 16:49.554
There are even three to four soups.

16:50.177 --> 16:53.258
We have braised pork ribs
and braised clams.

16:53.258 --> 16:56.178
And conch soup
and pork stomach and chicken soup.

16:56.777 --> 16:59.698
He even cooked bamboo shoot soup.
Oh, my goodness.

16:59.698 --> 17:01.337
(All the dishes
that we've talked about.)

17:01.337 --> 17:04.137
This is steamed fish with chili.

17:04.137 --> 17:05.202
Right.

17:05.857 --> 17:07.297
It's crispy-skinned fish in chili sauce.

17:07.297 --> 17:10.046
- You two, stop creating names for dishes.
- Don't pretend to know it all.

17:10.046 --> 17:11.097
She knows better than you.

17:11.097 --> 17:12.702
Yeah, that's true.

17:12.702 --> 17:16.337
Today, we can eat so many tasty dishes,
mainly because of Sheng.

17:16.337 --> 17:19.557
Sheng, how did you first get
into the traditional music circle?

17:20.458 --> 17:22.418
Initially, a friend asked me

17:22.418 --> 17:25.537
to rearrange a piece of music for her.

17:25.537 --> 17:27.637
Then I came to know about this circle.

17:28.658 --> 17:31.738
So did you join a club
or were you on your own

17:31.738 --> 17:33.010
at the very beginning?

17:33.566 --> 17:35.297
I was alone at first.

17:35.297 --> 17:39.658
Then the club leader approached me
after listening to several of my pieces.

17:39.658 --> 17:41.617
And then I joined the club.

17:41.617 --> 17:43.137
You're indeed talented.

17:43.137 --> 17:44.857
Her works are quite famous.

17:44.857 --> 17:47.537
Yes, I know.
We've probably all heard them.

17:47.537 --> 17:48.698
Yes, we have.

17:48.698 --> 17:50.458
We've all heard 'Return With You',
right?

17:50.458 --> 17:53.097
Besides, it's rare to find someone

17:53.097 --> 17:56.057
who can both compose and arrange music.
And she can also sing.

17:56.057 --> 17:59.337
How should I put it?
She's like an all-in-one machine.

17:59.337 --> 18:01.018
A rare genius.

18:01.018 --> 18:03.018
What metaphor is that?
An all-in-one machine?

18:03.018 --> 18:06.577
My singing really can't compare
with that of professionals.

18:06.577 --> 18:08.898
I mainly compose and arrange.

18:08.898 --> 18:10.537
You're being too modest.

18:10.537 --> 18:10.898
Right.

18:10.898 --> 18:12.218
How great it is to be able to compose!

18:12.218 --> 18:14.418
Many clubs don't have composers.

18:14.418 --> 18:14.658
Right.

18:14.658 --> 18:16.370
Your club leader is really lucky.

18:16.938 --> 18:20.537
I'll take the liberty to call the shots.
Sheng, you should join us.

18:20.537 --> 18:22.698
There's not only a dubbing club
at Tianzi No. 1 Recording Studio.

18:22.698 --> 18:26.018
We also have a traditional music club,
and the two of us are the leaders.

18:26.018 --> 18:28.698
Right, we're both leaders.

18:28.698 --> 18:32.458
Sorry. I'm really close
to the people in my club.

18:32.458 --> 18:33.537
Just come to our place...

18:33.537 --> 18:35.537
That's okay, Sheng.
They're just kidding.

18:35.537 --> 18:37.037
Stop talking nonsense.

18:37.577 --> 18:39.337
Not only is her club leader lucky,

18:39.337 --> 18:41.458
but they also have a keen eye.
We are not that fortunate.

18:41.458 --> 18:44.498
We can only envy.
We haven't found anyone like her.

18:44.498 --> 18:46.297
Here, the food is ready.

18:46.297 --> 18:48.178
- Thank you, Mo.
- Quickly join us.

18:48.178 --> 18:50.277
Shrimp-stuffed okra.

18:51.218 --> 18:53.018
Thanks for all the food.

18:53.018 --> 18:54.162
This is a feast.

18:54.698 --> 18:57.337
Well, let me say a few words.

18:57.337 --> 18:59.377
Thanks to Sheng,

18:59.377 --> 19:02.537
we could have such a feast

19:02.537 --> 19:04.458
prepared by Mo.

19:04.458 --> 19:05.297
Well said.

19:05.297 --> 19:06.817
Here's a toast to all.

19:06.817 --> 19:08.018
- Okay. Cheers!
- Cheers!

19:08.018 --> 19:09.617
Thank you, Sheng.

19:09.617 --> 19:11.218
- Thank you, Sheng.
- Thank you, Sheng.

19:11.218 --> 19:13.077
It feels like we are at your home.

19:16.377 --> 19:17.817
Let's start eating.

19:17.817 --> 19:19.418
I'll help myself.

19:19.418 --> 19:20.857
It's been a long time
since I've had fish.

19:20.857 --> 19:22.797
Didn't you say it smelled good?
Eat more.

19:25.777 --> 19:27.698
The bamboo shoot soup you made

19:27.698 --> 19:29.738
tastes just like the one at Wang's.

19:29.738 --> 19:30.537
Try some.

19:30.537 --> 19:31.570
I'll try it.

19:45.458 --> 19:46.518
Is it good?

19:52.418 --> 19:55.317
Aren't you guys eating?
If not, Mo will eat all the fish.

19:55.938 --> 19:56.978
Hurry.

19:56.978 --> 20:00.377
Mo's fish is second to none
in the world.

20:00.377 --> 20:01.418
It's tasty.

20:01.418 --> 20:02.478
Really?

20:27.018 --> 20:29.117
Hurry up. You're too slow.

20:29.738 --> 20:31.377
Don't be so hasty.

20:31.377 --> 20:34.777
If you think we're slow,
you could buy a mahjong machine.

20:34.777 --> 20:39.557
Right, from now on, we'll come every day
for the mahjong machine.

20:41.418 --> 20:43.498
I have an online event tonight.

20:43.498 --> 20:45.077
I'll escort you back home first.

20:47.938 --> 20:49.958
Let me get changed first.

20:50.577 --> 20:51.637
Okay.

20:57.418 --> 20:58.837
Then I'll go outside first.

21:01.458 --> 21:02.718
Hurry up.

21:03.658 --> 21:04.658
What's the use of this tile?

21:04.658 --> 21:05.658
Two of Circles.

21:05.658 --> 21:06.706
Fa Cai.

21:07.377 --> 21:10.777
Fa Cai? It broke your kong.
It's your turn now.

21:10.777 --> 21:14.777
- Sheng, coming? We just started.
- Do you want to play?

21:14.777 --> 21:16.057
- Come.
- Join us.

21:16.057 --> 21:17.097
No, thank you.

21:17.097 --> 21:19.357
I'm fine just watching you play.
I have juice here.

21:21.377 --> 21:22.450
Thank you.

21:27.418 --> 21:29.557
This place is pretty close
to the hospital.

21:30.817 --> 21:33.597
That's exactly why
I chose this neighborhood.

21:34.498 --> 21:37.377
It's roughly the same principle
my grandfather used.

21:37.377 --> 21:41.842
He bought his house because it was
within walking distance to the hospital.

21:42.857 --> 21:46.037
Being a doctor means
you have to be on call at any time.

21:46.857 --> 21:48.537
Ever since I found out
you were a doctor,

21:48.537 --> 21:51.438
I've come to understand
why you can't be online often.

21:52.938 --> 21:56.434
It was actually okay before,
but I got busier since graduate school.

21:57.018 --> 21:58.317
And even busier later.

21:59.978 --> 22:01.857
I'll take the bus back myself.

22:01.857 --> 22:03.458
Now is the rush hour
for getting off work.

22:03.458 --> 22:07.158
If you drive me, you might get stuck
in traffic and be late for your event.

22:08.258 --> 22:12.037
Then let's take the subway.
I won't get stuck in traffic or be late.

22:15.458 --> 22:19.137
(The train to Sanlinli
will soon arrive at the station.)

22:19.137 --> 22:21.898
(Please stand behind the safety line
while waiting.)

22:21.898 --> 22:24.738
(Sound and Soulmates)
(Please don't lean on or hold the door.)

22:24.738 --> 22:27.058
(Online judge: Qiang Qingci)
(Please mind your steps.)

22:33.378 --> 22:35.442
(Sound and Soulmates)

22:36.178 --> 22:38.658
When will your event start?

22:38.658 --> 22:39.678
It's 8:30 p.m.

22:41.898 --> 22:47.978
That's seven stops.
It takes about an hour for a round trip.

22:47.978 --> 22:51.077
Don't worry. I've calculated the time.
It won't delay the work.

22:53.537 --> 22:54.297
I need to take a call.

22:54.297 --> 22:57.978
Hurry up! I have to go back
and watch the online event.

22:57.978 --> 22:59.617
It's not too late.

22:59.617 --> 23:00.057
Hello?

23:00.057 --> 23:02.557
Tonight's judges are all big shots.

23:03.454 --> 23:03.978
Yes.

23:03.978 --> 23:05.158
I can't miss it.

23:05.898 --> 23:07.658
It's a voice-acting contest?

23:07.658 --> 23:10.898
Yes, and the judges invited tonight
are all famous dubbing actors.

23:10.898 --> 23:11.418
This year...

23:11.418 --> 23:14.458
You've surely heard many of their voices
but can't match them to the person.

23:14.458 --> 23:17.418
If I want to continue my studies,
it'll be next year. I'm busy this year.

23:17.418 --> 23:19.037
I'm exhausted.

23:20.978 --> 23:24.537
All right, I gotta go.
The subway train is coming.

23:24.537 --> 23:27.954
(Sound and Soulmates)

23:30.057 --> 23:30.898
Give me the backpack.

23:30.898 --> 23:31.817
Okay.

23:31.817 --> 23:32.857
It's crowded.

23:32.857 --> 23:33.938
Let's go.

23:38.617 --> 23:41.317
Excuse us. Thank you.

23:41.817 --> 23:45.857
(The next stop
is the People's Hospital Station.)

23:45.857 --> 23:49.978
(Passengers going to
the People's Hospital, please be ready.)

23:49.978 --> 23:53.097
(Please get off at the doors
on the right side.)

23:53.097 --> 23:58.198
(Please mind the gap between the train
and the platform when you get off.)

24:02.577 --> 24:06.898
Were they talking about the event
you're going to tonight?

24:06.898 --> 24:08.082
Yes.

24:09.337 --> 24:12.777
The industry has improved lately,
and more people know about it.

24:12.777 --> 24:15.877
In the past,
not many people know about it.

24:17.857 --> 24:22.158
Yeah, most of the discussions
were online in the past.

24:28.857 --> 24:33.918
When was the first time
you heard my voice?

24:36.738 --> 24:41.037
The second year
after the release of your first work.

24:43.817 --> 24:45.438
That's a pretty long time ago.

24:47.537 --> 24:51.698
Back then, I was only a few years
into the industry. Where were you then?

24:51.698 --> 24:53.758
I was in junior high school.

24:55.817 --> 24:57.478
We knew each other pretty early.

25:01.698 --> 25:03.277
Excuse me.

25:22.857 --> 25:26.277
Are you sure
you're not going to be late?

25:27.377 --> 25:30.398
I don't joke about work.

25:43.178 --> 25:45.557
(Why doesn't Geng Xiaoxing contact me?)

25:46.978 --> 25:49.117
(Did I say something wrong?)

26:01.377 --> 26:04.537
Cutting fruit is simple.
What's with all that noise?

26:04.537 --> 26:05.898
There's not even a fork.

26:05.898 --> 26:08.337
Are we going to eat or not?

26:08.337 --> 26:12.158
Why not?
If you two don't eat, I'll have it all.

26:14.097 --> 26:15.438
Your knife work is good.

26:18.777 --> 26:20.337
It's all yours. Eat up.

26:20.337 --> 26:21.498
What is he doing?

26:21.498 --> 26:22.938
What's wrong with him?

26:22.938 --> 26:23.998
I have no idea.

26:36.057 --> 26:37.202
Eat.

26:39.097 --> 26:40.617
You took a fork?

26:40.617 --> 26:42.198
You are so attentive today.

26:43.978 --> 26:45.258
Have a try.

26:45.258 --> 26:46.758
No problem at all.

26:50.377 --> 26:51.518
It's so sweet.

26:52.297 --> 26:53.317
Drama queen.

27:01.282 --> 27:02.738
(WeChat Zhou Zheng Picture)

27:15.018 --> 27:16.218
You ask him.

27:16.218 --> 27:19.277
- Why don't you ask?
- Doudou, you ask.

27:29.137 --> 27:31.037
(Zhou Zheng)
(Sorry, missent.)

27:33.218 --> 27:34.706
(Geng Xiaoxing)
(It's okay.)

27:39.097 --> 27:41.682
What are you looking at? Just eat.

27:42.857 --> 27:44.678
I'll cut some more for you later.

27:49.297 --> 27:51.438
This is really odd.

27:52.337 --> 27:54.817
Is he stressed out
about being single for so long

27:54.817 --> 27:57.714
while his good friend
just starts dating?

27:58.258 --> 28:01.117
You'll never figure out
what an older man is thinking.

28:01.858 --> 28:05.234
(Girl's Dorm Building 3)

28:12.097 --> 28:16.817
(My phone broke the other day.
I just got a new one.)

28:16.817 --> 28:18.077
(Let's meet up.)

28:33.577 --> 28:34.797
(Why?)

28:37.777 --> 28:39.597
Maybe I shouldn't send this?

28:43.458 --> 28:46.018
(They accidentally
dirtied the contract yesterday.)

28:46.018 --> 28:47.718
(We need to sign a new one.)

28:53.978 --> 28:55.877
(Can't you mail it?)

29:01.297 --> 29:04.918
(I'm passing by your school tomorrow.
How about we meet tomorrow morning?)

29:10.458 --> 29:13.918
(Alright then, let's say 10 a.m.
My class ends at that time.)

29:27.537 --> 29:28.918
What's so funny?

29:29.458 --> 29:30.018
What?

29:30.018 --> 29:31.557
Are you not going to the show?

29:32.258 --> 29:33.978
It's still early.
There's plenty of time.

29:33.978 --> 29:36.498
There is not.
Quickly change your clothes.

29:36.498 --> 29:38.938
The organizer wants you to wear glasses.

29:38.938 --> 29:40.537
Why? Why glasses?

29:40.537 --> 29:44.198
They said you look more handsome
in glasses.

29:46.658 --> 29:47.458
Okay, got it.

29:47.458 --> 29:48.297
Don't be late.

29:48.297 --> 29:49.586
Okay.

29:50.537 --> 29:52.557
Glasses or not, I'm always handsome.

29:58.458 --> 29:59.478
Be careful.

30:00.938 --> 30:02.178
So many people at this stop.

30:02.178 --> 30:04.498
It's a transfer station.
Of course there are a lot of people.

30:04.498 --> 30:05.877
Hold on tight.

30:06.817 --> 30:09.877
Do you want
to move a little further closer?

30:20.898 --> 30:22.797
There are two more stops.

30:28.018 --> 30:30.498
When we arrive, you can directly go up
after you get off the train.

30:30.498 --> 30:33.158
It's a five-minute walk
from Gate No. 2 to your school.

30:36.178 --> 30:40.530
If a stranger tries to talk to you
on the way, just ignore them.

30:42.498 --> 30:44.117
I'm not a child.

30:46.777 --> 30:48.458
Then I won't walk you upstairs in a bit.

30:48.458 --> 30:50.738
I must take the subway
on the other side right away.

30:53.458 --> 30:56.357
Next time, I'll definitely walk you
to your dorm building.

30:56.706 --> 31:00.158
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

31:00.158 --> 31:05.534
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

31:05.534 --> 31:07.602
♪ I love you ♪

31:08.738 --> 31:14.277
(We've been boyfriend and girlfriend
for over two hours now.)

31:17.178 --> 31:20.337
(Attention, passengers, we have arrived
at Jiaodong University Station.)

31:20.337 --> 31:21.018
We have arrived.

31:21.018 --> 31:24.337
(Passengers for this stop,
please take your belongings with you.)

31:24.337 --> 31:26.057
Okay, let's go.

31:26.057 --> 31:26.777
(Please exit in order.)

31:26.777 --> 31:29.178
Excuse me. Thank you.

31:29.178 --> 31:30.357
We'll also get off.

31:31.970 --> 31:36.146
(Jiaodong University)

31:38.498 --> 31:41.438
Maybe I should walk you up.

31:41.938 --> 31:44.698
Exiting the station
will require an extra fare.

31:44.698 --> 31:46.238
I can go up on my own.

31:47.777 --> 31:48.882
Alright.

31:50.458 --> 31:51.837
Then I'll be off first.

31:53.458 --> 31:54.018
Goodbye.

31:54.018 --> 31:55.037
Bye bye.

31:59.377 --> 32:00.658
Bye bye.

32:00.658 --> 32:01.718
See you.

32:10.562 --> 32:11.998
(Girl's Dorm Building 3)

32:11.998 --> 32:13.982
♪ I am with you ♪

32:13.982 --> 32:15.486
♪ I love you ♪

32:15.486 --> 32:19.486
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

32:19.486 --> 32:22.494
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

32:22.494 --> 32:26.482
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

32:27.057 --> 32:31.398
(Is this how my relationship
with Qiang Qingci started?)

32:32.798 --> 32:37.170
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

32:39.507 --> 32:41.790
(Cooperation Agreement)

32:41.790 --> 32:45.618
♪ I love you ♪

32:48.938 --> 32:50.718
I'm back.

33:06.137 --> 33:07.837
What are you two doing?

33:08.938 --> 33:09.898
Qi Yao.

33:09.898 --> 33:10.938
What's up?

33:10.938 --> 33:14.238
How did you and your boyfriend start?

33:14.857 --> 33:18.438
I mean, officially start.
Did he confess to you?

33:19.857 --> 33:23.857
At first, it was because he would chew
on straws and the ends of his pens.

33:23.857 --> 33:26.018
He would even chew
on the mouth of bottled drinks.

33:26.018 --> 33:29.978
I thought it was so silly and cute,
and it made my heart flutter.

33:29.978 --> 33:32.718
Well, your point...

33:33.694 --> 33:34.706
Peculiar.

33:35.377 --> 33:37.498
Feelings are hard to explain.

33:37.498 --> 33:39.978
And what makes
one's heart skip a beat varies.

33:39.978 --> 33:41.698
If it were the same for everyone,

33:41.698 --> 33:43.777
wouldn't they all like the same person?

33:43.777 --> 33:45.238
That's true.

33:46.377 --> 33:49.377
Before I was with him,
I thought I had an ideal type.

33:49.377 --> 33:52.718
But then I realized it didn't matter.
What matters is the feeling.

33:59.257 --> 34:01.257
Isn't there some contest today?

34:01.257 --> 34:04.217
Qiang Qingci and Juemei are judges.
Aren't you two watching?

34:04.217 --> 34:06.002
That's right. I forgot.

34:06.617 --> 34:08.918
I was planning to study.

34:09.818 --> 34:11.306
I'll watch with you for a bit.

34:11.330 --> 34:16.274
(Sound and Soulmates)

34:26.617 --> 34:27.978
This program team is so smart.

34:27.978 --> 34:29.858
They know today's judges
have lots of fans.

34:29.858 --> 34:31.998
They've even broadcast
the waiting scenes.

34:35.537 --> 34:39.318
So, Juemei's real name is Zhou Zheng.
That's a beautiful name.

34:41.657 --> 34:42.737
They insist I wear glasses.

34:42.737 --> 34:44.697
Xiao'ou. Hello, Shen.

34:44.697 --> 34:46.617
(Sound and Soulmates)
It's so uncomfortable to wear these.

34:46.617 --> 34:46.978
Tianyi.

34:46.978 --> 34:48.242
Hello.

34:49.338 --> 34:52.257
Mr. Juemei, long time no see.

34:52.257 --> 34:52.858
What do you mean?

34:52.858 --> 34:54.697
Didn't we just meet a few days ago
at Tianzi No. 1?

34:54.697 --> 34:55.697
I was just being polite.

34:55.697 --> 34:57.298
How are these glasses?

34:57.298 --> 34:59.198
You are quite handsome today.

34:59.198 --> 35:00.274
Really?

35:00.778 --> 35:03.057
Mr. Qiang is here.
Could you please come backstage?

35:03.057 --> 35:05.057
Okay, I got it. Mr. Qiang is here.

35:05.057 --> 35:06.717
Okay, you go ahead.

35:10.617 --> 35:12.537
Sir, let me check your microphone.

35:12.537 --> 35:13.697
Okay.

35:13.697 --> 35:14.737
Alright.

35:14.737 --> 35:16.498
Thank you.

35:16.498 --> 35:18.657
Mr. Juemei,
let me check your microphone.

35:18.657 --> 35:19.666
Okay.

35:22.530 --> 35:24.050
(Stuck to you)

35:25.737 --> 35:26.978
Wait a minute. I can handle this.

35:26.978 --> 35:28.018
You help them first.

35:28.018 --> 35:28.710
Okay.

35:28.734 --> 35:29.538
(WeChat Zhou Zheng)

35:29.538 --> 35:32.146
(Stuck to you)

35:38.298 --> 35:41.838
(Zhou Zheng)
(Sorry, I pressed the wrong button.)

35:44.697 --> 35:45.878
(It's okay.)

35:55.018 --> 35:57.394
Why are all the bullet comments
about Qiang Qingci?

35:57.978 --> 35:59.858
He isn't going to the scene, is he?

35:59.858 --> 36:02.438
He is.
But he probably won't go on stage.

36:03.537 --> 36:04.918
What does he look like?

36:06.697 --> 36:08.838
He's quite good-looking.

36:10.498 --> 36:12.434
Look at
how the comments are flooding in.

36:13.018 --> 36:15.018
I just saw Juemei
sending a message to someone.

36:15.018 --> 36:16.778
Was it his girlfriend?

36:16.778 --> 36:18.338
Does Juemei have a girlfriend?

36:18.338 --> 36:19.858
I don't think so.

36:19.858 --> 36:21.458
Does he have a girlfriend?

36:21.458 --> 36:23.998
How would I know?

36:26.210 --> 36:26.978
(Zhou Zheng)

36:26.978 --> 36:29.037
He has quite a good image.

36:31.106 --> 36:32.338
(WeChat Moqingcheng)

36:35.577 --> 36:37.177
Quite a few people are watching today.

36:37.177 --> 36:38.258
(I've arrived.)

36:40.994 --> 36:42.866
(Sheng: Okay.)

36:45.890 --> 36:47.186
(It's okay.)

36:47.938 --> 36:50.657
Nowadays, dubbing actors really
get more and more attention.

36:50.657 --> 36:53.237
That's great. Back in our days...

36:55.177 --> 36:56.798
Who are you two texting?

36:57.458 --> 36:58.757
- My dad.
- My mom.

37:00.617 --> 37:02.697
Was I telling my monologue?

37:02.697 --> 37:03.717
Look.

37:18.577 --> 37:21.318
Mr. Qiang, are you ready?

37:22.537 --> 37:24.157
Then we can start at any time.

37:32.378 --> 37:33.177
(It's about to start.)

37:33.177 --> 37:36.597
Look at the comments. Everyone's talking
about Qiang Qingci and Juemei.

37:37.602 --> 37:39.410
(Okay.)

37:41.898 --> 37:44.438
(Have fun. I'm getting prepared.)

37:47.257 --> 37:48.378
(Okay.)
Just as I thought,

37:48.378 --> 37:51.677
they're all fans
of the Perfect Voice Studio.

37:52.338 --> 37:57.878
Hello, all the viewers at the scene
and those watching the live broadcast.

37:59.298 --> 38:03.338
This is the live broadcast
of the Sound and Soulmates Contest.

38:03.338 --> 38:06.378
Today is our first stop of the contest.

38:06.378 --> 38:09.778
(Sound and Soulmates)
On the big screens on both sides

38:09.778 --> 38:12.338
are the real-time comments
and interactions

38:12.338 --> 38:15.318
(Sound and Soulmates Contest Live Room)
from online friends.

38:17.057 --> 38:19.177
They're all fans of our judges.

38:19.177 --> 38:20.898
First,

38:20.898 --> 38:26.057
let me introduce our five judges
for tonight.

38:26.057 --> 38:26.938
(They are...)

38:26.938 --> 38:27.737
Just as I thought.

38:27.737 --> 38:28.537
(Miss Zhang Xiao'ou.)

38:28.537 --> 38:29.778
My idol won't show up.

38:29.778 --> 38:31.137
(Mr. Shen Ming.)

38:31.137 --> 38:32.657
(We look forward to your review)

38:32.657 --> 38:34.298
Hello, everyone. I'm Shen Ming.

38:34.298 --> 38:36.757
Mr. Zhou Zheng.

38:41.737 --> 38:44.958
Hello, everyone.
I'm Zhou Zheng, aka Juemei Shayi.

38:46.458 --> 38:47.137
He's so handsome.

38:47.137 --> 38:48.757
(Mr. Zhao Tianyi.)

38:48.898 --> 38:50.866
(Juemei, look at me!
Mr. Tianyi, I love you!)

38:52.097 --> 38:57.077
And Mr. Qiang Qingci,
whom you've all been looking forward to.

38:57.617 --> 38:59.597
Hello, everyone. I'm Qiang Qingci.

39:01.057 --> 39:03.438
My idol has appeared.

39:04.217 --> 39:06.418
His voice is too pleasant to the ear.

39:06.418 --> 39:08.338
I'm so envious of you, Sheng.

39:08.338 --> 39:11.257
Sheng, won't Qiang Qingci
be on stage tonight?

39:11.257 --> 39:12.978
No, he won't.

39:12.978 --> 39:16.217
Next, let's welcome
our first contestant of today.

39:16.217 --> 39:19.798
Du Qiufei.
Let's give her a warm welcome.

39:19.966 --> 39:21.586
(Sound and Soulmates)

39:25.257 --> 39:26.818
Hello, everyone. Hello, dear judges.

39:26.818 --> 39:29.217
I'm contestant No. 1, Du Qiufei.

39:29.217 --> 39:30.898
The performance
I'm bringing for you today

39:30.898 --> 39:33.657
is an excerpt
from A Lifetime in Jiangnan.

39:33.657 --> 39:37.130
I'm so looking forward to it.
Now let's hand the stage over to her.

39:37.154 --> 39:40.434
(Sound and Soulmates)

39:42.978 --> 39:44.722
(When I planned to avenge you, )

39:45.458 --> 39:47.197
(I thought about this.)

39:48.577 --> 39:52.946
(If Shen's army failed
and was finally annihilated, )

39:53.342 --> 39:54.858
(I'd definitely be caught.)

39:54.858 --> 39:58.137
Sheng, someone's
mentioning your name. Look.

39:58.137 --> 39:58.938
Let me quit now.

39:58.938 --> 40:00.338
- No.
- Hang on.

40:00.338 --> 40:01.438
It's okay.

40:01.978 --> 40:04.257
Everyone thinks we're here
to watch the show. It's okay.

40:04.257 --> 40:05.537
Plus, quitting looks intentional.

40:05.537 --> 40:06.918
Exactly.

40:07.234 --> 40:08.418
(Two-way love)

40:08.418 --> 40:11.217
I also have a spare account. So...

40:11.217 --> 40:13.498
No. The ID of 'Shengshengman'
has already appeared.

40:13.498 --> 40:15.298
If you exit now, it will be even worse.

40:15.298 --> 40:17.022
It's okay. Just stay put.

40:17.022 --> 40:18.938
- Stay calm and eat noodles.
- It's fine.

40:18.938 --> 40:21.097
(Then I could get my revenge.)

40:21.097 --> 40:22.642
(I shouldn't have been born.)

40:23.217 --> 40:24.958
My fate has been cursed.

40:26.057 --> 40:30.398
In Jiangnan, it was you who bound me.

40:31.298 --> 40:32.838
I survived

40:33.697 --> 40:37.878
because you were born that year.

40:41.137 --> 40:44.670
Thank you, Chen Shaojie,
for your wonderful performance.

40:44.670 --> 40:46.617
First, we'll invite all the contestants

40:46.617 --> 40:49.938
who have just appeared
to come back on stage.

40:49.938 --> 40:52.978
Next, we will invite Qiang Qingci
to give comments online

40:52.978 --> 40:55.006
(for our first group of contestants.)

40:55.006 --> 40:56.057
- Qiang Qingci is here.
- Nice.

40:56.057 --> 40:57.478
Welcome.

41:00.577 --> 41:02.737
These are tonight's
first group of contestants.

41:02.737 --> 41:05.818
Some of the contestants
presented us with great voice-acting.

41:05.818 --> 41:08.938
It was very powerful,
with good rendering of lines.

41:08.938 --> 41:11.058
(But why didn't they get high scores?)

41:11.617 --> 41:14.177
(Actually, the opinions of us judges
are the same.)

41:14.177 --> 41:16.018
(Your voices are all pretty good.)

41:16.018 --> 41:19.398
But your interpretation of the lines
was a bit too superficial.

41:19.978 --> 41:23.778
Every character has their own feelings
and background of growth.

41:23.778 --> 41:27.298
Even when they speak,
due to their own personality and stance,

41:27.298 --> 41:30.438
their mental activity
and purpose in speaking vary.

41:31.057 --> 41:33.057
(Of course, we might haven't given you)

41:33.057 --> 41:35.697
(all this background information
in detail.)

41:35.697 --> 41:37.798
(But this is where you can improvise.)

41:38.418 --> 41:40.077
Let me give you a small example.

41:40.737 --> 41:43.737
For a line for a character,

41:43.737 --> 41:46.117
I remember one contestant
interpreting it this way:

41:46.978 --> 41:50.557
"I shouldn't have been born.
My fate has been cursed."

41:51.137 --> 41:52.498
That's exactly the same.

41:52.498 --> 41:53.978
It's exactly like that contestant's.

41:53.978 --> 41:57.378
No, to be precise,
although the timbre is a bit different,

41:57.378 --> 42:01.557
the tone, the pause, and the feeling
are all the same.

42:02.338 --> 42:04.518
"You were born that year."

42:09.378 --> 42:11.298
It does sound
very tragic and sad this way.

42:11.298 --> 42:14.298
But if the emotion is too exaggerated,

42:14.298 --> 42:17.978
if the actor is too eager
to affect the audience with their voice,

42:17.978 --> 42:21.978
it actually lacks the emotional impact
that can move the audience.

42:21.978 --> 42:25.057
What really moves people
is the character's own emotions.

42:25.057 --> 42:26.657
So trust me,

42:26.657 --> 42:30.117
a normal person
wouldn't speak like that.

42:30.617 --> 42:34.677
This line can be interpreted
in various ways.

42:35.338 --> 42:39.878
For example, you can show self-mockery
and self-loathing.

42:43.938 --> 42:45.518
I shouldn't have been born.

42:47.298 --> 42:49.358
(My fate has been cursed.)

42:51.657 --> 42:56.518
In Jiangnan, it was you who bound me.

42:59.057 --> 43:00.518
(I survived)

43:02.737 --> 43:05.037
because you were born that year.

43:14.257 --> 43:18.237
(You can also choose to express
the guilt about the past)

43:19.177 --> 43:20.918
and the hope deep within.

43:27.697 --> 43:29.237
I shouldn't have been born.

43:31.057 --> 43:32.717
(My fate has been cursed.)

43:36.097 --> 43:39.597
In Jiangnan, it was you who bound me.

43:43.378 --> 43:44.717
I survived

43:46.378 --> 43:48.478
because you were born that year.

44:21.506 --> 44:25.438
♪ Where should I start
about millions of dawns and dusks ♪

44:25.438 --> 44:26.302
♪ Depict a stroke ♪

44:26.302 --> 44:27.486
♪ Of rain before the mountain ♪

44:27.486 --> 44:30.014
♪ Stars beyond the sky ♪

44:30.014 --> 44:34.366
♪ Bit by bit, it outlines
yesterday and today ♪

44:34.366 --> 44:36.670
♪ And you with
picturesque eyebrows and eyes ♪

44:36.670 --> 44:39.006
♪ Jointly create the mood ♪

44:39.006 --> 44:43.262
♪ The rain and fog
over the mountains are intriguing ♪

44:43.262 --> 44:45.246
♪ It seems I can't get enough of seeing ♪

44:45.246 --> 44:48.062
♪ The once inexhaustible journey ♪

44:48.062 --> 44:49.118
♪ On this journey ♪

44:49.118 --> 44:50.974
♪ The stars accompany me
along thousands of miles ♪

44:50.974 --> 44:53.278
♪ I walk down with you ♪

44:53.278 --> 44:57.918
♪ Spending dawns and dusks together
for a hundred years ♪

44:57.918 --> 44:59.742
♪ Just like ♪

44:59.742 --> 45:00.766
♪ When the clouds are low ♪

45:00.766 --> 45:02.078
♪ It rains ♪

45:02.078 --> 45:06.494
♪ I was moved
when you were singing softly ♪

45:06.494 --> 45:10.174
♪ Since then, I hear stars every night ♪

45:10.174 --> 45:11.614
♪ And rains at midnight ♪

45:11.614 --> 45:16.126
♪ I could hear you
among millions of voices ♪

45:16.126 --> 45:18.622
♪ All other voices fade away ♪

45:18.622 --> 45:21.246
♪ I hear your monologue ♪

45:21.246 --> 45:25.246
♪ Saying I miss you so much ♪

45:25.246 --> 45:27.870
♪ Like knowing
the implied meaning of a picture ♪

45:27.870 --> 45:30.590
♪ And the emotions in your eyes ♪

45:30.590 --> 45:34.558
♪ Feel new even after several times ♪

45:34.558 --> 45:37.118
♪ Among the millions of people ♪

45:37.118 --> 45:39.934
♪ I hear your voice ♪

45:39.934 --> 45:43.806
♪ Saying I miss you so much ♪

45:43.806 --> 45:46.558
♪ A sky full of stars
all over the mountains and fields ♪

45:46.558 --> 45:49.086
♪ You are my whole world ♪

45:49.086 --> 45:56.466
♪ Slowly spending
dawns and dusks with you ♪
